1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,580
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.

2
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:04,820
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.

3
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:06,660
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.

4
00:00:06,660 --> 00:00:09,980
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:13,110
[North Star Entertainment]

6
00:00:13,110 --> 00:00:14,980
[IQIYI]

7
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:17,180
[Present]

8
00:00:19,550 --> 00:00:26,510
♫Never met anyone who could make me understand this word♫

9
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:34,780
♫But when I met you, my heart started beating fast♫

10
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:43,180
♫You’re the only one in my heart who could make me feel this way♫

11
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:50,910
♫This long-awaitied moment is now over♫

12
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:56,350
♫From now on, my heart and soul will be yours for the rest of my life♫

13
00:00:56,350 --> 00:00:59,680
♫Always have each other, never let go♫

14
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:04,750
♫Trust in me ‘cause I’ll be by your side♫

15
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:09,780
♫Hold my hand, Baby♫

16
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:13,180
[Desires in the Wind]

17
00:01:13,260 --> 00:01:18,710
[Previously]
I solemnly vow to protect Princess Catherine to the best of my ability.

18
00:01:18,730 --> 00:01:20,700
Talk to Grace if you need anything.

19
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,700
She is my trusted servant.

20
00:01:23,730 --> 00:01:27,360
I heard a glass shattering. May I go inside to check if everything is all right?

21
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,480
Her Highness does not want to be disturbed at night.

22
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:34,509
Something’s fishy here. I’ll go take a look around the hotel just to make sure.

23
00:01:34,509 --> 00:01:35,680
Help!

24
00:01:38,860 --> 00:01:39,660
Princess!

25
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:40,729
The princess is safe.

26
00:01:40,930 --> 00:01:42,330
She’s resting inside.

27
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:46,680
Where were you during an incident last night, Miss Vayo?

28
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:52,110
I promise that I will do my best to keep you safe, even if I have to sacrifice my own life, Your Highness.

29
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,860
How is it, Helena?

30
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:22,060
Have you found anything suspicious about that cop?

31
00:02:24,260 --> 00:02:25,060
Nothing.

32
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:26,700
Are you sure?

33
00:02:27,860 --> 00:02:28,660
Yes.

34
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,160
But I don’t trust her.

35
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:32,800
She was nowhere to be seen during the incident last night.

36
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:36,500
She was supposed to be here to guard the princess.

37
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,460
What if she saw something she shouldn’t?

38
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:45,210
If that cop sniffs out something, she definitely won’t stay quiet.

39
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:48,650
But so far, I couldn’t see anything suspicious about her.

40
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,130
I agree with Helena.

41
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:54,900
Those men we hired also told me they already took care of the princess.

42
00:02:55,860 --> 00:03:00,780
I still don’t trust them, not until they send us pictures of the princess’s dead body.

43
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,210
I have a bad feeling about this.

44
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:11,010
Then I’ll keep an eye on that cop and run some background checks on her.

45
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:15,000
If she finds out about our plan, get rid of her.

46
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,400
Is that the one who took the princess?

47
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:36,760
Follow her.

48
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:41,180
We have to kill the princess before Mr. Henri finds out she’s still alive.

49
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,930
You call that a tailing? Idiots!

50
00:04:55,210 --> 00:04:56,080
Let’s go!

51
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:18,130
What?

52
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,530
Women’s and men’s toilets are connected.

53
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,200
Damn it!

54
00:06:29,730 --> 00:06:30,530
Mew.

55
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,700
Lom, what took you so long?

56
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:35,500
I almost couldn’t stop that woman.

57
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,300
Now, I can’t even open the clinic.

58
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:38,560
Is she conscious now?

59
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:39,600
She’s been for a while.

60
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,260
Kept asking for you the moment she woke up.

61
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,560
When she knew you were gone, all she wanted was to get out of here.

62
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:47,060
I had to beg her to stay until the IV drip was done.

63
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:51,450
Thank you so much, my little cutie.

64
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,410
Miss Vayo.

65
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:12,100
Be careful.

66
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:34,050
Please don’t overdo it…I mean, force yourself, Your Highness.

67
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:38,010
My apologies. I’m not good with royal terms.

68
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:41,000
You can drop the formalities.

69
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:43,360
Just call me Miss Blew.

70
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:45,500
That way, no one would find it suspicious too.

71
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:57,050
You’re bleeding. I’ll go get the doctor.

72
00:07:57,909 --> 00:08:01,010
No need. I’m fine.

73
00:08:03,410 --> 00:08:06,280
If you don’t want to see the doctor, let me tend to it for you then.

74
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,210
Please allow me.

75
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:07,900
Thank you.

76
00:09:11,860 --> 00:09:14,730
Can you tell me what happened, Miss Blew?

77
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:21,760
After I drank the orange juice, I just passed out.

78
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,130
Passed out?

79
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:30,460
But…

80
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:44,210
Kill her. And don’t forget to send me proof.

81
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:45,260
Yes.

82
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:49,130
Grace!

83
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:50,300
Where are you going?

84
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,560
Don’t stop me!

85
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,080
I need to tell everyone.

86
00:09:53,330 --> 00:09:54,650
You can’t go now!

87
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,750
I need to tell everyone that Grace is a traitor!

88
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,200
But you can’t go now.

89
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,260
No one knows you’re missing–not the officials here or even your people from Madelin.

90
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:10,660
But I’m their crown princess!

91
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:13,260
Why hasn’t anyone noticed it?

92
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:25,010
Because right now, there’s an imposter who looks exactly like you taking your place as Princess Blew.

93
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:28,550
What? What do you mean?

94
00:10:30,060 --> 00:10:34,080
The imposter and your servants are in this together.

95
00:10:34,380 --> 00:10:36,780
She now has the power to order your people from Madelin.

96
00:10:37,210 --> 00:10:44,580
If you reveal yourself now without proof that you’re the real princess, we’ll blow our cover and become their target instead.

97
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:55,710
An imposter–who is she?

98
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:20,080
Unbeleivable.

99
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:26,580
From a death row prisoner to this beautiful and elegant princess.

100
00:11:26,950 --> 00:11:30,850
All my hard work is now paying off.

101
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:34,680
Those surgeries are surely worth the effort.

102
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:40,310
Even King Arthur wouldn’t know you’re not his real daughter.

103
00:11:44,060 --> 00:11:47,680
Are you sure our plan will work, Grace?

104
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:52,710
I’m not doing this because I want to be a princess.

105
00:11:52,710 --> 00:11:54,880
I just don’t want to die.

106
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,460
Do you think you have the right to choose?

107
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:02,550
You’re just a death row prisoner, waiting for your last day to come.

108
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:07,650
If I hadn’t saved you back then, you would’ve been dead long ago.

109
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:10,730
I know.

110
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:20,380
Remember, you are now Princess Catherine–the crown princess of Madelin.

111
00:12:21,130 --> 00:12:25,750
That’s your only job. Your opinions are not needed.

112
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,450
We’re here, Miss.

113
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:09,330
You can stay here for now while we’re evaluating the situation.

114
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:25,600
This way, please.

115
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,930
This is my safehouse.

116
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,200
No one knows about it.

117
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:50,200
How long do I have to hide here?

118
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:54,400
Until you can prove you’re the real Princess Catherine.

119
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:59,700
But I have dignity and grace. Why do I have to hide?

120
00:14:00,260 --> 00:14:03,310
You should be able to understand the situation more than anyone, Miss Blew.

121
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:07,810
I know. But there’s a traitor imposing as myself right now.

122
00:14:07,810 --> 00:14:09,510
If I don’t take any actions,

123
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:15,750
the fake princess might do something to harm my prestige and reputation or even my own country.

124
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,050
I’m just a commoner.

125
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:22,530
I wouldn’t understand anything about the royal prestige.

126
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:28,580
But as a cop who already vowed to protect you,

127
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,480
it is my duty to keep you safe as best as I can.

128
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:34,100
But I can’t–

129
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,330
I’m trying to help you here, Princess.

130
00:14:37,530 --> 00:14:41,160
I’d appreciate it if you'll cooperate and follow my advice.

131
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,100
It is for your own safety.

132
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:49,760
Excellent.

133
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:55,000
Father has never talked to me like that.

134
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,950
My apologies, Your Highness.

135
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,800
But should there be anything that might be harmful to you,

136
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,900
I beg you’d forgive me for overstepping.

137
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:28,260
Please don’t worry, Your Highness. You still have me and Henri to protect you.

138
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:32,580
Thank you, Grace, for always staying by my side.

139
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:39,880
[Door knocking]

140
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,400
Come in.

141
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,980
These are my clothes.

142
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,810
I hope you wouldn’t mind, Miss Blew.

143
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,200
Thank you.

144
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,500
Please make yourself at home.

145
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:13,360
You can always tell me if you need anything.

146
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:16,500
Miss Vayo.

147
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:18,130
Yes, Miss?

148
00:16:20,130 --> 00:16:22,300
Can I really trust you?

149
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:28,560
What do you think, Miss Blew?

150
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,150
I don’t know.

151
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:43,850
Even Grace, my most loyal and trusted servant all this time,

152
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,700
can betray me and try to kill me.

153
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:52,360
How could you trust someone you’ve just met, right?

154
00:16:58,260 --> 00:17:00,800
You don’t have to trust me now.

155
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:05,900
I’ll do my best to help you and keep you safe.

156
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:12,609
After everything is over, you can decide whether I’m sincere or not.

157
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:15,800
Let’s do that then.

158
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,349
Thank you.

159
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:22,780
Deal.

160
00:17:35,910 --> 00:17:38,580
[Dictator]

161
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:44,980
Yes, Dad?

162
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:48,510
What happened? Why were you absent on duty?

163
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:50,880
Why disappeared and abandoned your team like that?

164
00:17:52,260 --> 00:17:54,060
Who told you, Dad?

165
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:57,700
Henri, the royal guard from Madelin.

166
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:01,060
Henri?

167
00:18:02,530 --> 00:18:09,010
Yes, he insisted that us chiefs should keep an eye on our security team–

168
00:18:09,010 --> 00:18:11,810
especially the head of security which is you.

169
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:15,750
Tell me honestly, what have you done to upset them?

170
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:19,330
Nothing.

171
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:22,510
This is serious, Lom.

172
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:24,710
I don’t know what you’re up to right now.

173
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:27,950
But if it’s dangerous, you’d better stop.

174
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:33,550
Because if anything happens, even my position won’t be able to save you.

175
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:39,180
I know. If I ever do anything wrong, I’ll take sole responsibility for it.

176
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:43,180
I promise I won’t get you into trouble. I have to go now

177
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:46,050
Lom! Lom!

178
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:00,460
Here you go.

179
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:05,050
That kid is unbelievable–so stubborn and impetuous. She never listens to me.

180
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:10,360
Seriously, do you really not know whom she takes after?

181
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:15,060
Are you saying she’s like me?

182
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:21,810
Yes. Don’t you remember you were younger? You were pretty wild like a bull too.

183
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,580
Don’t tell me you can’t remember.

184
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:28,560
No matter what, you’re taking her side anyway.

185
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:36,700
Look, it’s my new recipe. I’ve never done it before. Please try it for me.

186
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:39,350
Here.

187
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:40,400
Come then.

188
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,310
Is the dressing good?

189
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:45,410
I can’t believe I'm doing this.

190
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:45,910
What?

191
00:19:45,930 --> 00:19:47,600
Getting mad at our daughter while pleasing her mother.

192
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,460
Even the tomato tastes good.

193
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,780
I’m being targeted by those from Madelin.

194
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:04,500
What do you mean?

195
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,800
Henri, the royal guard, is watching my every step.

196
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:13,200
After today, I’m afraid I won’t be able to come here anymore.

197
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,400
Not until your imposter leaves this country.

198
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:23,780
Henri has long served our family as a loyal and honest servant.

199
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:28,780
Even his father, Antoine, has always been loyal to my father.

200
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:33,210
I wonder what makes him trust Grace and agree to do something terrible like this.

201
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:36,780
Power and money can always change people.

202
00:20:42,660 --> 00:20:45,460
If what Grace has now are an imposter who looks like me,

203
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:48,080
my family’s royal heirloom,

204
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,350
and also Henri as her conspirator;

205
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:56,210
I’m afraid a chance to prove that I’m the real princess of Madelin

206
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:58,550
is almost impossible.

207
00:21:01,130 --> 00:21:02,560
But you still have me.

208
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:15,460
What makes you certain that I’m the real Princess Blew?

209
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:23,260
Because among the similarities, there’s one thing that’s different.

210
00:21:29,330 --> 00:21:30,130
What is it?

211
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:36,200
Your eyes.

212
00:21:41,730 --> 00:21:47,480
There’s this shining in your eyes which I’ve never seen in anyone.

213
00:21:49,310 --> 00:21:58,150
They make me feel that you’re someone special.

214
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:36,660
Yes, Khem?

215
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:40,160
Our informant already tracked down that cop’s phone.

216
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:43,350
Now we know where she is. What’s next?

217
00:22:43,530 --> 00:22:46,810
Good. We must get rid of them.

218
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:48,000
Let’s go, guys!

219
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,100
Something in my eyes look special?

220
00:23:08,900 --> 00:23:14,010
Then, will Father recognise me?

221
00:23:22,260 --> 00:23:23,350
Come in.

222
00:23:26,930 --> 00:23:29,850
I got summoned and must be at the hotel immediately.

223
00:23:30,210 --> 00:23:33,680
The imposter has altered the schedule and will leave tomorrow morning.

224
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:39,000
But that’s not the original plan. Why did she change it?

225
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:41,910
I’m not sure either.

226
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,700
Please go then. I’ll wait here.

227
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:52,310
I’ll be back by late morning tomorrow.

228
00:23:52,310 --> 00:23:54,950
Please wait for me here. Don’t go out anywhere.

229
00:23:58,130 --> 00:23:59,510
Please be careful.

230
00:24:25,930 --> 00:24:28,000
Hey, what’s up, Lom?

231
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:31,180
I’m on my way. Might be a bit late.

232
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:34,210
Take care of the princess for me while I’m not there.

233
00:24:35,730 --> 00:24:37,100
What do you mean?

234
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:41,610
Huh? I thought we got summoned.

235
00:24:42,130 --> 00:24:44,460
because the princess has moved up her schedule to leave for Japan.

236
00:24:46,260 --> 00:24:50,550
Moved up her schedule? How come no one told me that?

237
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:52,650
Our team hasn’t been informed either.

238
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:54,910
Did Chief tell you that?

239
00:24:58,500 --> 00:24:59,980
Nothing. I’m hanging up.

240
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,550
Don’t leave any trace.

241
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:25,980
The princess must not come out alive tonight.

242
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:32,010
Khem and I will go round the back. The rest of you take the front.

243
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:05,510
Come out, Princess.

244
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:10,910
Please trust me.

245
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:08,710
Miss Vayo!

246
00:29:32,350 --> 00:29:33,750
Go, Khem!

247
00:29:34,350 --> 00:29:36,110
Miss Vayo!

248
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:20,950
Listen, brat! There’s nowhere to run.

249
00:30:21,060 --> 00:30:24,180
Just hand her over to me.

250
00:30:26,530 --> 00:30:28,900
I’ll go. I don’t want you to be in trouble.

251
00:30:29,010 --> 00:30:31,250
No, we’ll get through this together.

252
00:30:31,250 --> 00:30:33,950
My car is that way. Go and wait there.

253
00:30:34,250 --> 00:30:35,250
Go!

254
00:30:40,530 --> 00:30:41,330
Khem!

255
00:30:43,930 --> 00:30:45,150
Let’s go!

256
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:16,200
I’m sorry I put you in danger, Miss Blew.

257
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,730
It’s not your fault, Miss Vayo.

258
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:23,260
We never know who else is working for Grace.

259
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:25,930
But I already promised you.

260
00:31:28,060 --> 00:31:30,180
And I’m still safe.

261
00:31:30,180 --> 00:31:35,110
I’m still alive, all because you’ve saved my life again.

262
00:31:35,980 --> 00:31:37,310
But…

263
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:40,280
Thank you.

264
00:31:47,900 --> 00:31:49,760
Those marks on your neck…

265
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:59,810
If it weren’t for you, I would’ve surely reunited with my ancestors.

266
00:32:01,300 --> 00:32:02,730
But how would you reunite with them?

267
00:32:06,100 --> 00:32:09,910
Well, that’s not what it’s supposed to mean.

268
00:32:09,910 --> 00:32:11,350
Never mind then.

269
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,100
What is it? I want to know.

270
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:21,850
By reuniting with ancestors, I mean ‘Ded’.

271
00:32:26,130 --> 00:32:26,930
Ded?

272
00:32:30,260 --> 00:32:32,950
Yes, as in ‘Dead’. Dead.

273
00:32:34,260 --> 00:32:36,200
Then, you’re not allowed to do that.

274
00:32:36,900 --> 00:32:38,880
You have to stay with your new family.

275
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:43,060
New family? What do you mean?

276
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:47,800
I mean you’re not allowed to die.

277
00:33:05,130 --> 00:33:08,060
As you wish, Your Highness.

278
00:33:14,010 --> 00:33:18,810
So, what should we do now?

279
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:24,480
I guess we need a new hideout.

280
00:33:27,950 --> 00:33:33,010
[Bangkok-Chaing Mai]

281
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:31,159
Please excuse me, Your Highness.

282
00:35:13,660 --> 00:35:15,460
What’s the name of that damn cop?

283
00:35:16,130 --> 00:35:17,000
Lieutenant Lom.

284
00:35:17,600 --> 00:35:21,500
Have our men track her phone right now. I need to know where she’s going.

285
00:35:25,150 --> 00:35:26,280
Move!

286
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:59,250
Where are we?

287
00:35:59,330 --> 00:36:01,000
On our way to Chiang Rai.

288
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:03,800
Once we’re there, someone will pick us up.

289
00:36:04,930 --> 00:36:08,700
Chiang Rai? The northern part of Thailand?

290
00:37:02,860 --> 00:37:03,910
Come.

291
00:37:09,930 --> 00:37:11,350
Hey, Din.

292
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:14,780
Lom, what happened?

293
00:37:14,780 --> 00:37:16,250
Why did you need someone to pick you up?

294
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:18,750
And why can’t I tell Uncle Thit you’d come?

295
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,700
It’s a long story. I’ll tell you later.

296
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:24,700
So…

297
00:37:26,460 --> 00:37:28,910
So…

298
00:37:29,260 --> 00:37:31,650
Miss Blew, this is Din, my oldest sister.

299
00:37:33,660 --> 00:37:36,080
It’s a pleasure to meet you, Miss Din.

300
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:41,050
Well, why don’t we go talk inside?

301
00:37:43,100 --> 00:37:43,900
Let’s go.

302
00:37:56,130 --> 00:37:57,410
Water, Miss.

303
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:05,750
Water, Miss.

304
00:38:09,010 --> 00:38:10,750
Ahem!

305
00:38:26,530 --> 00:38:31,760
So, who’s this Miss Blew? Why can’t I tell Uncle Thit you’re here?

306
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:35,730
Miss Blew is someone I have to take care of.

307
00:38:39,560 --> 00:38:40,360
Your new girl?

308
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:48,650
Oh, you’re here, Lom?

309
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,160
I just finished arranging the room for you.

310
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:53,930
Rose, say hello to Miss Blew, Lom’s girlfriend.

311
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:56,850
Aww, you’re taken now?

312
00:39:03,530 --> 00:39:05,010
Princess!

313
00:39:09,160 --> 00:39:12,810
What, Rose? That’s Lom’s girlfriend.

314
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:20,310
No, she is Princess Catherine Blew De Laina of Madelin!

315
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:25,850
Calm down, Rose.

316
00:39:26,060 --> 00:39:29,780
She’s Miss Blew, Lom’s new girlfriend. You’ve mistaken her for someone else.

317
00:39:30,260 --> 00:39:31,810
No, I’m not!

318
00:39:32,100 --> 00:39:36,560
She is–I saw her on the royal news. It’s during her visit to Thailand.

319
00:39:37,100 --> 00:39:40,160
I even told you she looks so elegant, remember?

320
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,750
Spit it out.

321
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:01,850
Well, I have to take care of her–as a bodyguard.

322
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:16,250
I’m glad you can recognise me, Miss Rose.

323
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:18,900
But can you please keep it a secret?

324
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:20,660
Of course, Your Highness.

325
00:40:21,530 --> 00:40:24,410
Din, hurry up and pay respect to her.

326
00:40:44,860 --> 00:40:47,280
We need to talk, now!

327
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,880
Can I hold your hand, Your Highness?

328
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:01,310
So beautiful.

329
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:03,960
Thank you.

330
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:07,400
This is a national matter, Lom!

331
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,310
Yes.

332
00:41:09,310 --> 00:41:11,450
If Miss Blew hadn’t been sitting here,

333
00:41:11,450 --> 00:41:15,150
I would’ve never believed something so serious like this is really happening.

334
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:21,100
Who on earth would’ve imagined that the princess they see on the news every day is actually an imposter?

335
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:30,800
Din, can you please not tell my dad about this?

336
00:41:32,060 --> 00:41:36,880
But I think this matter is getting out of hand and too big for you to handle.

337
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:40,010
Maybe you should ask your dad for help.

338
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:45,680
You know what my dad is like. Do you think he’ll believe me?

339
00:41:46,060 --> 00:41:48,730
He’d probably send Miss Blew back to Madelin.

340
00:41:51,060 --> 00:41:53,360
He’d say it has nothing to do with our country.

341
00:41:54,860 --> 00:42:00,650
How are you going to prove that you’re the real princess, Miss Blew?

342
00:42:00,650 --> 00:42:03,810
I really can’t see a way out right now.

343
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:09,060
Neither can I.

344
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:24,460
But for now, keeping her safe is my first priority.

345
00:42:33,730 --> 00:42:35,600
I’ll try to evaluate the situation on that side too.

346
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:39,980
We might need to stay here for a few days.

347
00:42:42,260 --> 00:42:44,300
You can stay as long as you want.

348
00:42:45,060 --> 00:42:49,310
I’m just worried those thugs might find out you’re here.

349
00:42:49,330 --> 00:42:51,560
They even know where your safehouse is.

350
00:42:52,460 --> 00:42:55,850
Don’t worry, I already sent them somewhere far away.

351
00:43:14,700 --> 00:43:15,860
Please wait here for a second.

352
00:44:07,330 --> 00:44:08,730
- Let’s go.
- Where did you go?

353
00:44:10,600 --> 00:44:11,400
Come on.

354
00:44:22,730 --> 00:44:24,680
Hey! Did you find them?

355
00:44:24,700 --> 00:44:25,660
Not a soul here!

356
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:29,650
Khem! What about you?

357
00:44:29,730 --> 00:44:32,580
Not yet. I’ve searched every community in the area.

358
00:44:33,050 --> 00:44:35,880
Damn it! And I came all the way here to the middle of nowhere.

359
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:37,810
We have to find them no matter what!

360
00:44:37,810 --> 00:44:40,380
Our informant has tracked down the phone’s location and said it’s here.

361
00:44:40,380 --> 00:44:44,580
So, they must be here. Go find them!

362
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:48,250
You’re such a badass!

363
00:44:48,260 --> 00:44:51,860
You lured them to the furthest south when you’re actually at the other end of the country!

364
00:44:52,660 --> 00:44:54,750
Well, no big deal. I’m an expert.

365
00:44:55,600 --> 00:45:00,280
Expert? Is that because you usually have to keep juggling your dates?

366
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:03,910
Hey, be nice. That’s not it.

367
00:45:04,550 --> 00:45:07,980
I mean when catching criminals. What juggling dates?

368
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:22,130
You must be tired now, Miss Blew. You should probably get some rest.

369
00:45:28,500 --> 00:45:31,530
You should get some rest too. We’ll talk later, okay?

370
00:45:35,260 --> 00:45:36,080
Okay.

371
00:45:36,600 --> 00:45:40,100
Let me take care of the princess. I’ll take her to her room.

372
00:45:43,730 --> 00:45:44,530
Thank you.

373
00:45:45,800 --> 00:45:47,210
Let’s go then, Your Highness.

374
00:46:05,460 --> 00:46:07,050
Please come in, Your Highness.

375
00:46:15,700 --> 00:46:19,700
You can drop the formalities, Miss Rose. Just call me Miss Blew.

376
00:46:20,100 --> 00:46:22,180
But you’re the princess, Your Highness.

377
00:46:22,180 --> 00:46:25,150
I’m afraid it would be inappropriate to speak casually with you.

378
00:46:26,060 --> 00:46:29,900
You have my permission. You’re now my friend, Miss Rose.

379
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:31,560
Yes, Your Highness.

380
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:40,480
I’ve finished arranging the room for Miss Blew, Miss.

381
00:46:41,930 --> 00:46:42,580
Okay.

382
00:46:43,580 --> 00:46:45,880
This is Buakiang, the housemaid.

383
00:46:49,130 --> 00:46:52,400
If you need anything, you can always let her know.

384
00:46:55,700 --> 00:46:59,300
I need a bruise relief cream. Do you possibly have it?

385
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:04,880
Yes, we do. May I ask if you’re hurt anywhere?

386
00:47:04,880 --> 00:47:07,150
Do you need me to help tend to the wound?

387
00:47:08,300 --> 00:47:13,360
That’s all right, I’m fine. It’s for Miss Vayo. She got hurt because of me.

388
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:17,410
I’ll have Buakiang bring you the medicine then.

389
00:47:25,360 --> 00:47:26,560
Please make yourself comfortable.

390
00:47:36,100 --> 00:47:37,350
Here it is, Miss.

391
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:52,310
Miss Rose said apply it thinly in the morning and evening. The bruise should be fading away in a few days.

392
00:47:52,310 --> 00:47:55,680
After a week, it should look as good as new, Miss.

393
00:47:57,200 --> 00:47:58,850
Thank you.

394
00:47:58,850 --> 00:48:03,510
If you ever need anything, you can always tell me, Miss.

395
00:48:25,400 --> 00:48:26,580
Miss Blew.

396
00:48:30,530 --> 00:48:31,960
I brought you medicine.

397
00:48:35,300 --> 00:48:36,600
Thank you, Your Highness.

398
00:48:43,130 --> 00:48:44,650
Hold on, Miss Blew.

399
00:48:49,100 --> 00:48:51,860
I was about to go see you too.

400
00:48:53,800 --> 00:48:56,500
Why? Do we have to run again?

401
00:48:57,500 --> 00:49:02,910
No, I just want to talk about the plan–about what we should do next.

402
00:49:03,610 --> 00:49:06,180
I don’t want Din and Rose to get involved.

403
00:49:08,930 --> 00:49:10,930
Then, let’s talk in your room.

404
00:49:14,060 --> 00:49:16,610
Sure. Please come in.

405
00:49:25,330 --> 00:49:28,260
Is there a Thai embassy in Madelin?

406
00:49:28,730 --> 00:49:30,780
As far as I know, there doesn’t seem to be any.

407
00:49:31,960 --> 00:49:36,280
No, I intend to discuss this matter during my visit here.

408
00:49:36,530 --> 00:49:38,560
I want to foster friendly relations between our countries.

409
00:49:39,800 --> 00:49:47,850
Unfortunately, if only there were a Thai embassy in Madelin, it would’ve been easier to send the news to your father.

410
00:49:50,200 --> 00:49:55,910
Actually, there’s a way to contact Father without drawing Grace and her followers’ attention.

411
00:49:57,010 --> 00:49:57,910
But…

412
00:49:58,200 --> 00:49:59,060
But what?

413
00:50:00,100 --> 00:50:02,910
I want to make sure of the situation on that side first.

414
00:50:03,280 --> 00:50:08,610
I don’t know if Antoine–Herni’s father–is also involved in this conspiracy.

415
00:50:10,400 --> 00:50:18,450
If he finds out that I’m still alive, I fear my father’s and brother’s lives would be in danger.

416
00:50:22,760 --> 00:50:24,560
Please don’t worry about that.

417
00:50:25,700 --> 00:50:26,960
I’ll look into this matter for you.

418
00:50:27,800 --> 00:50:29,200
I have a cousin who’s a reporter.

419
00:50:29,560 --> 00:50:30,800
She knows a lot of informants.

420
00:50:31,300 --> 00:50:32,700
It might not be that hard to find out.

421
00:50:33,460 --> 00:50:34,260
Really?

422
00:50:38,260 --> 00:50:40,460
Let’s address each problem one at a time.

423
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:43,330
I’m sure we’ll finally get through this.

424
00:50:44,760 --> 00:50:46,300
I do hope so too.

425
00:50:48,060 --> 00:50:49,800
I want it to be over as soon as possible,

426
00:50:50,900 --> 00:50:52,130
for the sake of everyone’s safety.

427
00:50:55,330 --> 00:50:57,300
Right now, you should go get some rest first.

428
00:50:59,260 --> 00:51:02,160
As long as I’m here, you’ll be safe.

429
00:51:05,360 --> 00:51:08,760
Make sure to apply that medicine, Miss Vayo.

430
00:51:11,500 --> 00:51:13,660
I’ll do it now then, or else I might forget.

431
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:25,750
Let me help.

432
00:52:21,900 --> 00:52:26,750
If possible, please don’t get hurt for me again.

433
00:52:28,500 --> 00:52:30,300
I can’t promise you that.

434
00:52:34,060 --> 00:52:35,300
Did you even listen?

435
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:43,410
I can’t promise you because it’s something unforeseen.

436
00:52:44,350 --> 00:52:48,850
If there’s an encounter, it’s hard to avoid getting injured.

437
00:52:54,860 --> 00:52:57,300
But there’s one thing I can promise you.

438
00:53:01,300 --> 00:53:08,150
As long as I’m here, I’ll never let anyone hurt you.

439
00:53:11,700 --> 00:53:15,160
I’ll protect you with my own life.

440
00:53:26,760 --> 00:53:27,560
Grace!

441
00:53:27,860 --> 00:53:28,660
Grace!

442
00:53:29,800 --> 00:53:31,880
Prince Karel is calling. What should we do?

443
00:53:32,060 --> 00:53:34,650
Stop panicking. Just answer the call.

444
00:53:34,650 --> 00:53:37,280
We’ve rehearsed this, remember? What are you afraid of?

445
00:53:37,360 --> 00:53:38,410
I can’t do it.

446
00:53:47,560 --> 00:53:49,130
It’s Grace, Your Highness.

447
00:53:50,660 --> 00:53:54,610
The princess is engaged at the moment and unable to take the call.

448
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:59,080
I’ve called her many times but she didn’t pick up.

449
00:53:59,480 --> 00:54:01,010
Is she not feeling well?

450
00:54:02,160 --> 00:54:06,850
The princess is doing well, Your Highness. It’s just that her schedule is rather hectic these days.

451
00:54:07,460 --> 00:54:11,380
But I also texted her. She didn’t respond to any of them.

452
00:54:11,500 --> 00:54:13,300
Please tell her to call me back.

453
00:54:14,500 --> 00:54:15,480
Yes, Your Highness.

454
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:27,360
Is he suspicious of anything?

455
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:28,850
No.

456
00:54:29,180 --> 00:54:33,750
Henri, those men you sent to kill the princess, did they really finish their job?

457
00:54:33,750 --> 00:54:36,150
Why haven’t I seen any proof yet?

458
00:54:36,300 --> 00:54:39,000
They just disappeared. I’ve been trying to get ahold of them.

459
00:54:39,330 --> 00:54:42,280
Or are they avoiding you because they messed up?

460
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:48,080
If the hitmen messed up and let the princess get away, wouldn’t we all be screwed?

461
00:54:55,730 --> 00:54:57,480
I shouldn’t have agreed to do this.

462
00:54:58,060 --> 00:55:00,460
You know how my father is someone King Arthur trusts–

463
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:02,930
a loyal and honest secretary.

464
00:55:04,500 --> 00:55:07,330
If he finds out I’m in this with you to overthrow the king,

465
00:55:08,600 --> 00:55:10,200
he’d never let me live.

466
00:55:11,860 --> 00:55:13,980
Antoine would never know.

467
00:55:14,600 --> 00:55:16,280
Don’t worry, Sweetie.

468
00:55:17,260 --> 00:55:18,960
Think about our future.

469
00:55:19,930 --> 00:55:24,050
When King Arthur is gone and Helena finally takes the throne,

470
00:55:24,300 --> 00:55:28,100
you will get to be a royal secretary instead of your controlling father.

471
00:55:29,330 --> 00:55:36,250
You’ll finally have freedom to yourself. And everything in Madelin will be ours.

472
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:40,130
Will it be that easy?

473
00:55:40,960 --> 00:55:44,300
Just get rid of the princess and everything will be over.

474
00:55:45,930 --> 00:55:51,310
Your job right now is to find those men and make the princess disappear.

475
00:55:54,900 --> 00:55:58,860
Fah, it’s Lom. Can you do me a favour?

476
00:55:59,500 --> 00:56:02,130
Hey, how can I help you, Sis?

477
00:56:03,330 --> 00:56:05,380
I want information on Madelin.

478
00:56:06,960 --> 00:56:09,500
That’s odd. Is there something wrong?

479
00:56:15,130 --> 00:56:16,810
Is it that serious?

480
00:56:18,800 --> 00:56:20,600
If that’s true, it’s going to hit the headlines for sure.

481
00:56:21,530 --> 00:56:23,760
Yes, that’s why I don’t trust anyone.

482
00:56:24,660 --> 00:56:28,610
Do you have any informant who might be able to sniff around in Madelin right now?

483
00:56:29,100 --> 00:56:31,460
Leave it to me. I’ll take care of that.

484
00:56:32,460 --> 00:56:35,880
I guess I’ll have to cover this scoop about the princess myself.

485
00:56:36,260 --> 00:56:39,800
I really want to see how smoothly this imposter can act as a princess.

486
00:56:40,930 --> 00:56:43,050
I’ll try to gather more evidence.

487
00:56:43,050 --> 00:56:45,950
If I find anything, I’ll call you to meet later.

488
00:56:46,260 --> 00:56:48,100
It’s not safe to talk about this over the phone.

489
00:56:49,200 --> 00:56:51,510
I’m counting on you then. Thanks a lot.

490
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:59,850
[Thai Human Imagery Museum]

491
00:58:21,260 --> 00:58:24,260
Reporters here are so annoying! Why keep following me around and taking so many photos?

492
00:58:24,500 --> 00:58:25,760
It makes me uncomfortable.

493
00:58:27,600 --> 00:58:29,960
There’s a media asking for an interview with you today.

494
00:58:30,760 --> 00:58:35,330
I won’t do it. Don’t you think we should hurry and get out of this country before we’d get exposed?

495
00:59:10,760 --> 00:59:12,980
Do you like Iris, Miss Blew?

496
00:59:15,730 --> 00:59:18,100
I never expect I’d see these flowers here.

497
00:59:18,700 --> 00:59:20,910
You can pick them. Miss Rose wouldn’t mind at all.

498
00:59:22,560 --> 00:59:26,580
That’s fine. They just remind me of home.

499
00:59:27,930 --> 00:59:30,480
Are there Irises in Madelin too?

500
00:59:33,560 --> 00:59:36,980
Iris is my signature flower.

501
00:59:37,550 --> 00:59:42,250
Father said I’ve loved them since when I was very little.

502
00:59:42,750 --> 00:59:46,880
So, he told the servants to plant them around my place.

503
00:59:53,100 --> 01:00:03,780
Iris is a flower of valor and elegance. It symbolises the eyes of heaven.

504
01:00:07,300 --> 01:00:12,950
Now I know why your father chose Iris as your signature flower.

505
01:00:14,060 --> 01:00:16,330
But if I can’t resolve this situation…

506
01:00:17,460 --> 01:00:21,650
and allow my imposter to commit more crimes,

507
01:00:22,900 --> 01:00:24,360
Father would certainly be disappointed in me.

508
01:00:29,130 --> 01:00:38,310
Strong, sturdy, and elegant–you are all of that, Miss Blew. You will definitely defeat those traitors.

509
01:00:42,530 --> 01:00:50,010
However strong or sturdy I am, I fear there’s no way to reclaim my elegance.

510
01:00:52,600 --> 01:00:57,450
For I am now only a princess without her crown.

511
01:00:58,700 --> 01:01:04,410
If your old crown got stolen, just find a new one as a temporary replacement.

512
01:01:06,700 --> 01:01:08,130
Where can I find it then?

513
01:01:14,260 --> 01:01:16,110
Please allow me.

514
01:01:52,760 --> 01:01:57,010
This flower crown might not be a perfect replacement.

515
01:01:58,580 --> 01:02:06,410
But if you are born a princess, no matter where you are–in my eyes–you will always be a princess.

516
01:02:10,160 --> 01:02:12,580
And you will always shine with elegance.

517
01:02:24,560 --> 01:02:31,910
[Next Episode]
I appreciate everything you’ve done for me. But from now on, you are no longer needed in my life.

518
01:02:32,460 --> 01:02:38,360
Not that I don’t trust Dad, Din. It’s those around him and his subordinates–I don’t trust any of them.

519
01:02:39,210 --> 01:02:40,650
Go! Go! Go!

520
01:02:43,300 --> 01:02:44,330
Please leave without me, Your Highness.

521
01:02:44,530 --> 01:02:46,100
But you’ll be in danger, Mr. Wathit.

522
01:02:47,400 --> 01:02:48,880
Drop the gun!

523
01:02:50,500 --> 01:02:52,980
Hide and seek is over, Princess.

524
01:03:07,950 --> 01:03:12,410
♫From now on, my heart and soul will be yours for the rest of my life♫

525
